				\begin{document}$$ \left( {\text{NSAF}} \right)k = \frac{{\left( {\frac{SpC}{L}} \right)k}}{{\mathop \sum \nolimits_{i = 1}^{N} \left( {\frac{SpC}{L}} \right)i}} $$\end{document}NSAFk=SpCLk∑i=1NSpCLiwhere the total number of MS spectra matching peptides from protein k (SpC), was divided by the protein’s length (L), then divided by the sum of SpC/L for all N proteins [14]. The pathway analysis was generated through the use of QIAGEN’s Ingenuity Pathway Analysis (IPA, QIAGEN Redwood City, CA, USA) to identify the canonical pathways associated with the dataset [15].
